<h2>1.9 - What is new in OpenBSD 5.3?</h2>
d387 3
a389 3
The complete list of changes made to OpenBSD 5.2 to create OpenBSD 5.3
can be found on <a href="../plus53.html">plus53.html</a>, and highlights
on the <a href="../53.html">OpenBSD 5.3 Information page</a>, however
d391 1
a391 1
warrant some special note to people upgrading or installing OpenBSD 5.3
d396 6
a401 6
<li><b><a href="http://www.opensmtpd.org">OpenSMTPD</a> is ready for
production use!</b><br>
New installations should consider using OpenSMTPD as their mail
transport agent.
Existing installs should look at using OpenSMTPD to replace sendmail,
as at some point in the future, sendmail will probably be removed.
d403 5
a407 6
<li><b><a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=dhclient&amp;sektion=8">dhclient(8)</a>
improvements:</b><br>
dhclient-script eliminated, HUP signals cause the client to reread the
configuration files and obtain a new lease, killing dhclient will
attempt to remove routes and addresses it had configured, and lots of
other improvments.
