<h2>1.9 - What is new in OpenBSD 5.1?</h2>
d380 3
a382 3
The complete list of changes made to OpenBSD 5.0 to create OpenBSD 5.1
can be found on <a href="../plus51.html">plus51.html</a>, and highlights
on the <a href="../51.html">OpenBSD 5.1 Information page</a>, however
d384 1
a384 1
warrant some special note to people upgrading or installing OpenBSD 5.1
d388 15
a402 32
<li><b>Synaptics touch pad support:</b><br>
The Synaptics touchpads (used on many laptops) have greatly improved
support now, through the
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=synaptics&amp;sektion=4">synaptics(4)</a>
device and the
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=synclient&amp;sektion=1">synclient(1)</a>
utility.
You may even find OpenBSD provides better support for your trackpad
than the OS that came pre-loaded on your laptop!

<li><b>Base system and Xenocara manuals are now installed as source
code.</b><br>
This makes grep(1) more useful in <tt>/usr/share/man/</tt> and
<tt>/usr/X11R6/man/</tt>.
If both formatted and source versions of a manual page are installed,
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=man&amp;sektion=1">man(1)</a>
automatically displays the newer version of each page.

<li><b>midicat(1) removed:</b><br>
MIDI files can be manipulated and MIDI thru boxes can be created with
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=aucat&amp;sektion=1">aucat(1)</a>.

<li><b>ccd(4) removed:</b><br>
If you were using ccd(4) for concatinated or mirrored disks, you will
need to rebuild using
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=softraid&amp;sektion=4">softraid(4)</a>.

<li><b>Advanced notice: RAIDframe is going away.</b><br>
While RAIDframe is still in OpenBSD 5.1, it will NOT be in OpenBSD 5.2,
so if you are using it, you will need to start thinking about migration
to another solution, most likely
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=softraid&amp;sektion=4">softraid(4)</a>.
d477 4
a480 2
The license on
newer versions is unacceptable.
d529 1
a529 1
