<h2>1.9 - What is new in OpenBSD 4.9?</h2>
d377 3
a379 3
The complete list of changes made to OpenBSD 4.8 to create OpenBSD 4.9
can be found on <a href="../plus49.html">plus49.html</a>, and highlights
on the <a href="../49.html">OpenBSD 4.9 Information page</a>, however
d381 1
a381 1
warrant some special note to people upgrading or installing OpenBSD 4.9
d385 23
a407 15
<li><b>NTFS (read only)</b><br>
is now enabled on GENERIC i386 and amd64 kernels

<li><b>Wireless improvements</b><br>
WPA keys can now be specified using the simpler hostname.if format of:
<blockquote><pre>
nwid myssid wpakey wpapassword
</pre></blockquote>

<li><b>New <a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=rc.d&amp;sektion=8">rc.d(8)</a>
mechanism</b><br>
can be used for starting, stopping and reconfiguring
<a href="faq15.html">package</a> daemons, which can be used instead of
or in addition to modifications to <tt>/etc/rc.local</tt>.

