<h2>1.9 - What is new in OpenBSD 4.0?</h2>
d370 6
a375 5
The complete list of changes made to OpenBSD 3.9 to create OpenBSD 4.0
can be found <a href="../plus40.html">here</a>, however here are a few
changes the OpenBSD team anticipate will require or warrant some special
note to people upgrading or installing OpenBSD 4.0 who are familiar with
older versions:
d378 22
a399 27
<li><b>X Window aperture support now defaults to off</b>.
Those not using X will not care, those using X will need to deliberately
turn this on.
This was due to the demonstration of security issues due to X running
as a user process with kernel-like privileges.

<li><b><a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=cdio&amp;sektion=1">cdio(1)</a>
can now do track-at-once CD creation and CDRW blanking</b>.
This means many people will no longer need to install a third-party 
recording package.

<li><b>Hostname specific install set.</b>
The install and upgrade scripts now look for an install set named
siteXY-&lt;hostname&gt;.tgz.
E.g. for 4.0 an install on a host named 'puffy' will look for
site40-puffy.tgz wherever other sets are sought.
This is intended to allow easy per host customized installations,
upgrades, or disaster recovery.

<li><b><a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=ipsec&amp;sektion=4">IPsec</a>
improvements:</b>
see
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=ipsec&amp;sektion=4">ipsec(4)</a>,
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=ipsecctl&amp;sektion=8">ipsecctl(8)</a>,
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=ipsec.conf&amp;sektion=5">ipsec.conf(5)</a>,
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=sasyncd&amp;sektion=8">sasyncd(8)</a>,
and
d401 16
a416 1
for more details.
d418 3
a420 3
<li><b><a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=ifconfig&amp;sektion=8">ifconfig(8)</a></b>
now provides the functionality of the old spppcontrol(8) and
wicontrol(8).
d422 41
d465 1
d483 3
d570 1
a570 1
