<h2>1.9 - What is new in OpenBSD 3.8?</h2>
d357 2
a358 2
The complete list of changes made to OpenBSD 3.7 to create OpenBSD 3.8
can be found <a href="../plus38.html">here</a>, however here are a few
d360 1
a360 1
note to people upgrading or installing OpenBSD 3.8 who are familiar with
d364 30
a393 17
<li><b>Default shell for root is now 
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=ksh&amp;sektion=1">ksh(1)</a></b>,
instead of
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=csh&amp;sektion=1">csh(1)</a>.

<li><b>SSH Default key size has increased</b>, meaning slow systems
will take much longer to generate RSA/DSA keys on first boot.
Be patient.

<li><b>tx(4) has been replaced by 
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=epic&amp;sektion=4">epic(4)</a></b>.
If you have a network adapter using the SMC83C170 chip (such as the SMC
EtherPower II 10/100 cards), the driver that supports it has been
changed.
Before doing an upgrade, copy the <tt>/etc/hostname.tx*</tt> files to
corresponding <tt>/etc/hostname.epic*</tt> so the upgrade kernel can
recognize your adapter(s).
d497 1
a497 1
