text
@d362 1
a362 1
IF you chose to upgrade rather than reinstall, you must remove any
d364 1
a364 1
the upgrade, or you can render an i386 machine unable to boot in
d366 5
a370 8
This is due to the old Kerberos files being in
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=a.out&sektion=5">a.out</a>,
format and thus unable to run on the standard ELF kernel (which has
a.out emulations disabled, as mentioned above).
If you have encountered this problem, you need to
<a href="faq8.html#LostPW">boot into single-user mode</a> and edit
<tt>/etc/boot.conf</tt>, remove the offending lines, and reboot.
Removing the old krb4 modules would also be wise.
